main event: Radar returns and visual observations of unidentified flying objects near Goose Air Force Base in Labrador, Canada.
interesting points: Multiple radar operators and control tower personnel observed the unidentified objects, which exhibited rapid speed, sharp turns, and hovering capabilities.
The objects were described as round, luminous, and ranging in size from approximately 25-30 feet to 75 feet in diameter.
Attempts were made to establish radio contact with the objects, but were unsuccessful.
No known aircraft were in the area at the time of the sightings.
The sightings occurred over several days in September 1951 and were considered credible by investigators.
location: Goose Air Force Base, Labrador, Canada
